Calling all entrepreneurs, innovators, thinkers, and makers!

MakeSPP is a student-run hackathon and conference bringing together over 100 bright and curious minds. We're building a diverse and creative community to unleash the true potential of technology.

Pitch new ideas, meet fellow makers, and learn alongside amazing mentors. Join us!

FAQ


What is MakeSPP?

MakeSPP is a conference and hackathon with learning and building opportunities. Students will learn from amazing guest speakers, skilled mentors, and helpful workshops while working on their own innovative project.

What is a hackathon?

A hackathon is an event where you turn your creative ideas into a reality. Whether you're a future entrepreneur, programmer, or engineer, you and your team will have a chance to pitch your projects to judges and win over $1k worth of prizes.

Who can attend?

Any high school student in NJ or the Greater New York City area is free to partipate.

Is there a cost?

MakeSPP is 100% free thanks to our sponsors.

What if I'm a beginner?

Don't worry! We have several workshops to get you started. Be ready to learn a ton from mentors and have a lot of fun with your teammates!

What should I bring?

You should bring your materials for your project (optional), laptop, chargers, phone, your ID, and most importantly, ideas! All food, drinks, and snacks will be taken care of.

What if I don't have a team?

Don't worry! We'll have a team formation workshop at the beginning of the event.

Questions?

You can email us at team@makespp.com
